# Orchestrator — Update Customer Notes (Stage 3)

**Scope:** When the user runs **Update Customer Notes (UCN)** via **`10-task-router.mdc`**, execute the steps below **in order**. Treat any of these as **the same default pipeline** (including **Phase 0** — built-in Challenge Review), normalizing **`[CustomerName]`** like **`docs/project_spec.md` §2 Rule 4**:

- **`Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`**
- **`UCN for [CustomerName]`** or informal **`UCN`** / **`ucn`** when the customer is already fixed in thread context
- **`Update Customer Notes with Challenge Review first for [CustomerName]`** / **`Lifecycle-first Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`** (aliases; same behavior as default UCN)

**Opt-out (skip Phase 0 — legacy single STOP, Block B only):** Only when the user explicitly asks for **`Update Customer Notes (no challenge review) for [CustomerName]`**, **`UCN without challenge review for [CustomerName]`**, or **`Light UCN for [CustomerName]`**.

This is a **product-run playbook** for the **main Agent in this chat**; it does **not** replace **`.cursor/rules/core.mdc`** (task planning / approval expectations) or general engineering workflow choices.

**`_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E override (test-only):** when the run is **`Run E2E Test Customer`** for customer **`_TEST_CUSTOMER`**, execute this pipeline end-to-end without approval pauses for write tools (including `update_challenge_state`, `write_doc`, `append_ledger_row`, `sync_notes`). Keep normal approval behavior for all other customers/runs. See `.cursor/rules/11-e2e-test-customer-trigger.mdc`, `scripts/lib/e2e-catalog.txt` (harness SSoT), and `docs/ai/playbooks/tester-e2e-ucn.md` for the sequence and procedure.

## Built-in Challenge Review — Phase 0 (default)

**Plain English:** Saying **UCN** means the agent **reviews every open challenge** against transcripts and the saved lifecycle snapshot, shows **one review table**, and may propose **challenge status updates** to persist **after you approve**. You do **not** need to know file names or JSON; the agent handles persistence via MCP once you pick **Approve all**, **A only**, **B only**, or edits.

**When:** **Before pipeline Step 1**, unless **Scope — opt-out** applies.

1. Run challenge governance inline: read **`challenge-lifecycle.json`** via MCP **`read_challenge_lifecycle`**, merge ids + **last_updated** / state against **in-scope transcripts** (and the tracker table from **`read_doc`**), compute stall/drift per **`docs/ai/references/challenge-lifecycle-model.md`** (≥ 60 days since last transition on an unresolved state is a stall flag), and emit **one** review table with columns **`challenge_id | description | current_state | last_updated | evidence | stall / risk | recommended_action`**. Reuse data already loaded in orchestrator **Steps 2–3** where it is equivalent. When UCN is the parent run, **do not** use a **second** STOP for this — lifecycle write proposals are folded into **Block A** below.
2. Build **Block A — Challenge status updates** (implementation: MCP **`update_challenge_state`** rows: `challenge_id`, `new_state`, `evidence` citing **`call_id`** or lifecycle rule). Only **legal single-step** transitions per **`prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`**. Rows may be **zero**.
3. **Do not** call **`update_challenge_state`** until the combined approval step below.

**Steps 1–7** — Same as the default pipeline, with these **additions**:

- Treat **`MyNotes/Customers/[CustomerName]/AI_Insights/challenge-lifecycle.json`** (read via MCP **`read_challenge_lifecycle`**) as **+1** source when compiling **`challenge_tracker`** / exec narrative so **Block B** (mutation JSON) **does not contradict** Block A once both are approved.
- If the user will approve **Block B only**, Phase 0 still ran so the doc plan is **informed** by the review table; **skip executing** Block A in that case.

**STOP — combined user review (default UCN)**

Present in **one** message:

1. **Block A** — Table of proposed **`update_challenge_state`** rows (or **“none proposed”**).
2. **Block B** — Plain-language summary, **mutation JSON** for **`write_doc`**, proposed **ledger** row, and diff/summary per **`docs/ai/gdoc-customer-notes/mutations-global.md`**. **Before the real `write_doc`:** run **`scripts/ucn-planner-preflight.py`** as required in **`docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md`** Step 10. **Writer** `dry_run` / `--dry-run` (Doc preview) is **required** before each real write **only** for **`_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E** after preflight — **`docs/ai/playbooks/tester-e2e-ucn.md`** — not the default production step after the user already approved in Step 9.
3. Say explicitly: **Approve all (A then B), Block B only, Block A only, or reject / edit.** **No** **`update_challenge_state`**, **`write_doc`**, **`append_ledger`**, **`append_ledger_row`**, **`sync_notes`** for mutation purposes until the user answers.

**STOP — legacy (opt-out UCN only)**

After Step 7, if Phase 0 was **skipped**: present **Block B** only (summary, mutation JSON, ledger, plus preflight requirement per **`docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md`** Step 10) — same mutation gate as **`.cursor/rules/core.mdc`**. **No** **`update_challenge_state`** unless the user separately requested lifecycle writes.

**Execute (only after explicit approval)**

1. **If Block A approved (in full or in part):** run **`update_challenge_state`** once per **approved** row **before** any **`write_doc`**. Every call must obey the **Challenge lifecycle write rules** in **`.cursor/rules/21-extractor.mdc`** (TASK-048) — notably `transitioned_at` is the cited transcript's call date (not the run date) and `evidence` must be free of harness vocabulary from `FORBIDDEN_EVIDENCE_TERMS` in **`prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`**.
2. **If Block B approved:** run **`write_doc`** with MCP **`customer_name`** set to **`[CustomerName]`** whenever known (enables lifecycle ↔ Challenge Tracker parity checks **and** the TASK-050 §B lifecycle reconciliation pass in `update-gdoc-customer-notes.py` — the writer rewrites Challenge Tracker row `status` to match `challenge-lifecycle.json` `current_state` for every `[lifecycle_id:<id>]`-anchored row), then **`append_ledger_row`** (or **`append_ledger`** for the legacy GDoc ledger-append path). **Challenge Tracker rows** in the mutation plan must obey the **Challenge Tracker row discipline** in **`.cursor/rules/21-extractor.mdc`** (§B.1) — call-date `date` column, only transcript-backed evidence dates, no harness vocabulary. On every successful write the writer also appends one `appendix.agent_run_log` entry (TASK-050 §F) carrying `run_date`, `sections_touched`, `entries_added`, `entries_skipped`, `skipped_reasons`, `reconciled`, and — when the planner supplies them — `lookback_window`, `transcripts_in_scope`, `dal_prepends_emitted`; no run-log entry is written on rejection / zero-write runs (matches the "no ledger row on rejection" rule).
3. **Ledger recovery is mandatory before success:** if the ledger append call fails after a successful `write_doc`, run MCP **`read_ucn_recovery_state`** and then **`recover_ledger_from_latest`** (same customer + doc_id) before declaring the run complete. If recovery still fails, return blocked with the recovery state (`status`, `last_ledger_error`, `ledger_attempt_count`) and operator action; do not report success while state is `write_succeeded_ledger_pending` or `recovery_failed`.
4. Optional **`log_run`**, then **`sync_notes`** (when local mirror / Drive policy expects it), same as the default path.
5. If the user approved **Block B only**, **skip** step **1** entirely — still run steps **2**, **3**, **4**.

The narrative view of the account (Health line, call spine, milestones, challenge review, stakeholder evolution) now lives in **`Run Account Summary for [CustomerName]`** (**`docs/ai/playbooks/run-account-summary.md`**). UCN writes persisted state — **`challenge-lifecycle.json`**, the Google Doc, and the History Ledger — and nothing more.

